## 4. Mathematical Intuition

Suppose five modules all contain duplicated averaging logic.

Each implementation contains (k) lines:

[
\text{Duplicated code} = 5k
]

Moving the logic into one shared function reduces it to approximately:

[
k + 5
]

where the additional lines are imports or function calls.

Modules reduce duplication and make corrections easier. Fixing one shared function updates every caller.

