### `pyproject.toml`

```toml
[build-system]
requires = ["setuptools>=75"]
build-backend = "setuptools.build_meta"

[project]
name = "ml-utils"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "Reusable utilities for AI and ML learning"
requires-python = ">=3.11"

[tool.setuptools.packages.find]
where = ["src"]
```

Install the package locally:

```bash
pip install -e .
```

`-e` means editable mode. Source-code changes are immediately available without reinstalling.

Run:

```bash
python src/main.py
```

---

### Managing dependencies

Install libraries:

```bash
pip install numpy pandas matplotlib requests
```

Save installed versions:

```bash
pip freeze > requirements.txt
```

Install from the file:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Example:

```text
matplotlib==3.10.3
numpy==2.3.1
pandas==2.3.1
requests==2.32.4
```

Exact versions improve reproducibility but eventually require controlled upgrades.

---

### Time complexity

`calculate_mean()` reads every value:

[
O(n)
]

`calculate_range()` uses `min()` and `max()`:

[
O(n) + O(n) = O(n)
]

The package structure does not change algorithmic complexity. It improves organization and maintainability.

