## 8. Common Mistakes

### Running code outside the environment

You may install dependencies into one Python installation and run another.

Check:

```bash
python -c "import sys; print(sys.executable)"
```

### Naming files after standard libraries

Avoid filenames such as:

```text
json.py
requests.py
statistics.py
pandas.py
```

They can hide the real libraries.

### Circular imports

```text
module_a imports module_b
module_b imports module_a
```

This often indicates poor separation of responsibilities.

### Using `from module import *`

This hides where names originated and can cause collisions.

### Committing `.venv`

The environment directory is large and platform-specific.

Add to `.gitignore`:

```text
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
```

